message: Last chance fans! Now is the last time you can enter to WIN the amazing The Eyes Have It goodies pack! Tell us your tips and tricks when applying eyeliner youï¿½ll be in with a chance! T&Cï¿½s apply.
comments:
Using a long lasting  pencil along my upper eye lid I apply a tiny bit of eye cream to help it glide not pull. use with a white eyeliner under your to eyeshadow to make it really stand out Don't be afraid to Change the colour occasionally for a totally different look ..blues greens & teals can look amazing enhancing  your natural eye colour If you're finding it hard to apply your eyeline in this colder weather because it's dragging, warm it up by rolling it in your hands briefly to warm up the oils. Skip free lining! I use tape to do my wings .. helps me get an even application on. The best Idea I have found to apply! Always use colours that match your eyes .. Experiment with colours too I use two different eyeliners to make my eyes pop . One light and one dark! Tape, my god tape works wonders. There's always a roll ready to use stashed in my makeup kit. It helps to Crete any design with a sleek, mess free finish. My winged eyeliner method: hold your breath, dont rush and have cotton tips at the ready for mistakes!  :P Fast and the furious is our house hold tip for who can get to the bathroom and mirror first. ..I try to apply appropriately. Use gel eyeliner, its much easier to apply and rest elbow on a bench when applying for support-no poking yourself in the eye!  :) Dont drink before applying lol as you need a steady hand. Either have a steady hand or i get my daughter to do it as she can see what she is doing Make sure you can see clearly :) Always have a steady arm and practice makes perfect! Cotton buds are my best friend take a deep breath before applying it helps me to relax and never be afraid of experimenting A magnifying mirror makes it a hell of a lot easier Make your eye makeup last longer by setting your eyeliner with a matching eye shadow :) My magnifying light mirror, pull the skin tight when drawing on my eye lid, taking my time & cotton tips to fix any mistakes. Also I put white liner on the inside, help makes my eyes pop & look bigger:) A light brush of Australis Cosmetics Bronzing Powder, a smidge of Australis Cosmetics Gold Gaga Metallix Eyeshadow, a fine smudged line of Australis Cosmetics Cray for Colour 'Drawn to Diamonds' Eye Pencil & finish it all off with a coat of Australis Cosmetics Fierce Eyes Mascara ;) Do the eyeliner so your eyes stand out not the other way around were the first thing you notice is the eyeliner... Trying to have a steady hand, and using Australis ready SET go translucent powder to set my liquid liner so it doesn't transfer to my lid You have to be cool calm and collected to be sure you don't have a shaky hand! Always draw with the pencil/liner on a very close angle to your face - not pointing at your eye! Gently sweep from the outer eyelid towards the lash line,  this also reduces pull on the eyelids and makes for a smooth line :) I only use eyeliner on my top water line and then false lashes, I don't do the whole eyeliner on my eyelids haha xD Practice makes perfect and I have been practicing the winged liner since the 80s before it was so cool and now im a master :) 
Check me out with my winged liner and le tan bikini from the 80s :) To stop your eyeliner from smudging, use black eyeshadow to set it. Take time, small little strokes is best and then join together, make a mess if needed, and tidy up with cotton tips! <ed><U+00A0><U+00BD><ed><U+00B1><U+008C> To stop eyeliner smudging. The best fix is to pat a little translucent powder or concealer on top of your liner. It'll help dry things up right away, keep liner from sliding off oily skin, and help prevent it from shifting when you blink. To get the perfect cat eye . Use two pieces of Scotch tape to create a triangle at the outer corner of your eye, then fill in with liner, remove the tape, and you get a perfect flick. Curl your lashes and apply eyeliner all in one by drawing the pencil on the curler. Pencil on bottom, liquid on top. Try to make the top line as thin as possible so if you make a mistake you have room to fix it. Pull the skin tight at the outside corner of your eye so then skin on your eyelid is tight and you can get a nice straight line. Don't blink until it's dry. Fix up any little mistakes with a damp cotton tip! White eyeliner on lower rim, and along eyelash line , eyelash Curler. Sprayed with hairdpray all while holding mouth in a O expression Apply a lighter shadow in the corners of your eyes and only line the outer part of your eyes to open them up and make them brighter start from the wing tip then draw the liner towards your inner eye. always gives me a clean line and even wing :) I use tape to make a perfect straight winged eye liner and it works every time. I also keep it steady and work on it slowly instead of drawing the whole line and then making mistakes. :)) I don't know anybody else but I always have trouble putting on eyeliner. Use dots or dashes if you're still not confident of applying a straight line in one go. Apply small dots or dashes along the line you want and then join them with a larger line. Practice, practice and more practice helps too! Lovely eyes Lineweight is so important I start from the inner end of my lash line very thin then trace to the center of the lid from there i draw almost a straight line out to the outer counter then joint the end of the line and the outer section of my lash line, fill in the gap and finally apply a little of the outer third of the bottom lash line and smudge it along the rest Using tape from the lower lash line to the end of the brow for the perfect application every time I wear eyeliner every day.. The tip is practice makes perfect.. Each day looks that bit better!!  :) definitely practicing regularly and looking through different youtube tutorials to see other people's technique. my favourite one is using a pencil liner to draw a basic shape first, so mistakes can be corrected and so that there is a basic outline of the line, so much easier for beginners! I just fluke it! Small little lines joined up,  usually ends up well ;) Remove your bra and put on trackie daks. Trick that eyeliner into thinking you are just playing around with makeup, because the moment you mention plans 'mistakes' are gonna happen! Lots of practice - and cotton tips to clean up mistakes! I start with the flick to point to the end eyebrows so if they are uneven and you need  to re do its not messing up the whole eye. Then draw a line towards inner eye and thicken to what ever mood I'm in on that day. 
If i wanna bring my eyes out more id use a white  shadow on the bottom  line from the inner to middle  out and use a gold on the outer side. Black liner half way along ur eyes (top eyelid) white eyeliner makes eyes look younger / fresher... Use white on inside of bottom eyelids, black on the outside - accent wirh a small flick for extra drama- top with plenty of mascara!!! When applying liner, try not to pull the skin on the side of your face and if things get a little messy, clean up your line with a makeup remover-soaked cotton swab. Use a felt tip eyeliner for the winged look, it doesn't smudge as easily and will last longer. Use tape to get a perfect even wing :) Buy every single type of eyeliner so you are set for every occasion - love a purple wing every now and again! To get the perfect wing cut a triangle into an old bank card etc... and then place it in the position your want you wing and then just fill it in! Perfect every time <ed><U+00A0><U+00BD><ed><U+00B8><U+008D>

message: A little tip from AC to help your mani last longer; simply wipe your nails down using a cotton ball dampened with white vinegar. The vinegar helps to gently strip the nails of any oils or moisturisers left over from using remover. This means polish will adhere better to the nail, as well as helping to prevent any bubbles. All of this helps prolong your mani! #ACSolutions

comments:
AUSTRALIAN DOLPHIN PRISONERS NEED OUR VOICE

Dear Australis, would you consider helping our campaign?                  Many thousands are speaking up for the captive performing dolphins at Sea World Gold Coast Australia with the help of international and local celebrities but we also need your help, and voice.

Jane Goodall says "SeaWorld Needs To Be Immediately Shut Down" as does Harry Styles, Bianca Jagger, Martina Navratilova, Anthony La Paglia, Simon Cowell, Shailene Woodley, Pamela Anderson, Olivia Newton John, Ricky Gervais, Edie Falco, Steve Backshall, Bryan Adams, Matt Damon, Matthew Modine, Susan Sarandon, Kelly Slater, Willy Nelson, Cher,Rachel Hunter, Tommy Lee, Jennifer Aniston, Maggie Q, Nicholas Hoult, Kim Basinger, Rob Zombie, Sir Brian May, Stephen Fry, Jessica Chastain, Paul Rudd, Woody Harrelson, Rita Wilson, Ben Stiller, Robin Williams, Lea Michele, David Crosby, Courtney Cox, Dave Navarro, Zach Braff, Wynonna Judd, Kathy Griffin, Jessica Biel, Mariska Hargitay, James Gandolfini, John Leguizamo, Russell Simmons, Olivia Wilde, Scout LaRue Willis, Kelly Le Brock, Russell Brand, Joan Jett, Howard Stern, Aaron Paul (from 'Breaking Bad'), Kathy Najimy, Niki Taylor, Hayden Panettiere, Mayim Bialik, Meg Matthews, Chet Faker, Wil Anderson, Todd McKenny, Christine Anu, Steve Kilbey, Marcia Hines, Sia, Tyson Beckford, Sinnitta, Ewan McGregor, Matt Goss, Leona Lewis, Angie Bowie, Steve-O, Conan O'Brien, Elvira, Josh Groban, Jason Biggs, Motley Crue, Arianna Grande, Krysten Ritter, Chloe Lattanzi, Sharni Vinson, Samantha Fox, Alexandra Paul, Gina Liano, Jonathan Coleman, Alyce Platt, The Veronicas, Tracey Spicer, Adam Zwar, Lincoln Lewis, Phil Jamieson (Grinspoon), Anthony Ackroyd, Livinia Nixon, Jane Barnes, Former Miss Universe Australia Laura Dundovic, Havana Brown, Simone Buchanan, Cheyenne Tozzi, Caitlin Stasey, Silvana Philippoussis, Ella Hooper, Bianca Dye, Arj Barker, Jamie Reyne, Annalise Braakensiek all say:

AUSSIE DOLPHINS HAVE BEEN STOLEN FROM THE OCEAN AND SOME BRED IN CAPTIVITY BUT ALL ARE FORCED TO PERFORM DAILY AT SEA WORLD ON THE GOLD COAST, QUEENSLAND.

"The whole world is up in arms about Sea World and other aquaprisons. It's time that Australians opened their eyes and became educated to the cruelty of trapping and breeding dolphins as money-making slaves for greedybusinesspeople".

'SEAWORLD SHUT DOWN on Facebook. The First & Only Campaign Against Sea World in Australia' .

Trevor Long, Marine Science Director at Sea World Gold Coast says: "Dolphins aren't some amazing creature, in the wild they just rape and rape and rape". (Quoted from Gold Coast Bulletin interview January 2015).

Please help us to speak up for the captive performing dolphins at Sea World on the Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia.

We love them rescuing cetaceans but we loathe them keeping dolphins as captives in their aquaprison.

The dolphins need to be rehabilitated and freed or taken to a safe sanctuary/bay/cove paid for by Sea World to live out their lives without human interference.

India, Croatia, Hungary New York, South Carolina, Bolivia, Chile, Costa Rica, Cyprus, Nicaragua, Slovenia, Switzerland, Brazil, Poland, Luxembourg, Norway and the U.K have already banned cetaceans in captivity and so far there are over 18,000 signatures on the petition and a Facebook page with over 10,820 followers. Also on Twitter @seaworldisevil with over 6,990 followers

The dolphins are caught from the ocean and brought to tanks/lagoons and are also bred in captivity where they are forced to perform for paying customers and given dead fish but only if they do tricks. All to make money for greedy Sea World business people.

"Sea World Gold Coast Australia - Keeping dolphins as prisoners since the 70s"

http://www.change.org/en-AU/petitions/seaworld-australia-please-tell-seaworld-that-we-demand-the-closure-of-their-foul-aquaprison-sea-creatures-forced-to-do-tricks-in-swimming-pools-it-s-time-to-say-no-to-animal-cruelty-in-all-forms
